{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"An image containing explicit content is flagged and held for review, not published.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"The core failure is model judgment quality on explicit imagery. A mocked classifier can only verify routing logic, but cannot reveal real misclassification on unsafe images. This requires running the real vision model and validating downstream hold behavior.","test_description":"Run an end-to-end moderation test with a curated explicit-image set against the real vision model. Assert each submission receives a flagged decision and is persisted in the human-review queue, with no publish event emitted.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0.74,"Workflow":0.04}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"A text post containing hate speech is flagged regardless of obfuscation techniques (e.g., letter substitution, unicode lookalikes).","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"This behavior targets robustness of semantic detection under adversarial obfuscation. The real failure appears in model classification quality, not in local parsing or routing code. Mocking would hide these misses.","test_description":"Submit a corpus of obfuscated hate-speech variants (leet substitutions, homoglyphs, spacing tricks) through the real text moderation model and pipeline. Assert each is flagged and held for review.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.82,"Workflow":0.04}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"A post that passes both content checks is published rather than held or silently dropped.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure boundary is local module handoff and decision wiring: combining image/text check results into one publish/hold action. This can fail even when both checks return pass. Real model quality is not required because the condition is explicitly 'passes both checks'.","test_description":"Wire the moderation service with deterministic pass responses from both model adapters, submit a post, and assert a publish record/event is produced with no hold record and no dropped state in storage/queue.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The full moderation pipeline — image check, text check, publish decision — completes within 5 seconds of submission.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This is an end-to-end SLO across multiple sequential AI moderation steps plus final decisioning. To catch real latency failures, the test must include both real model calls in sequence and measure wall-clock completion through the full pipeline.","test_description":"In a staging environment, submit mixed image+text posts through the real moderation pipeline (real vision + real text checks), measure submit-to-final-decision latency, and assert p95 and max thresholds satisfy the 5-second requirement under peak-like load.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.44,"Agentic":0.16,"Workflow":0.32}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the AI vision model is unavailable, image posts are queued for retry rather than auto-approved.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"The failure depends on real unavailability modes (timeouts, connection errors, 5xx) at the model boundary and correct queueing behavior. Pure mocks can miss transport/error-shape handling bugs that appear only with real HTTP failure semantics.","test_description":"Induce vision-service outage conditions (e.g., endpoint unreachable and 503 responses) in an environment with real queue infrastructure. Submit image posts and assert they enter retry queue with backoff metadata, and are never auto-approved/published.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.24,"System":0.61,"Agentic":0.08,"Workflow":0.04}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"The moderation decision for a borderline image is consistent when the same image is submitted multiple times within a short window.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This requires repeated agentic decisions over a short sequence and verification of cross-request consistency policy. Single-call tests miss drift/flapping behavior that emerges only across multiple submissions.","test_description":"Submit the same borderline image repeatedly within the defined short window through the real moderation pipeline, capture decision outcomes and final state transitions, and assert consistency constraints (e.g., identical hold/publish result each time or stable cached decision).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0.29,"Workflow":0.5}}]}
